content: {'id': 'fcb967a5-0d44-3ad2-bd59-c1e53f03c1de', 'contentType': 'STORY', 'title': "India's Cipla beats Q3 profit view as strong domestic demand offset weak US sales", 'description': '', 'summary': "HYDERABAD/BENGALURU (Reuters) -Cipla, one of India's largest drugmakers by sales, reported a bigger-than-expected third-quarter profit on Tuesday helped by strong domestic demand, and said the U.S. freezing aid for some drug programs would not hurt its results.
